<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRESIDENT CLINTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * As a naturalized citizen of this great country, I am baffled by the citizens 
here who take so much for granted and seem to pay little or no attention to the 
details of any news story unless it involves scandal or celebrities. The shabby 
treatment of President Clinton by the media and his "low job-approval" rating 
by the masses are very sad and symptomatic of a seemingly childish and 
shallow-minded population. 
</P>
<P>
 Here is a very good man trying to bring several issues to the table concerning 
crime, health care and economic recovery, and because there is a struggle in 
his efforts to make changes that are good for the people, those same people 
seem to look at the surface, feel that the whole thing is messy, and dismiss 
this President as someone who is not doing a good job. 
</P>
<P>
 In previous years, people were cranky because the economy was sour and there 
was a general sense that President Bush did not care about domestic issues. Now 
it seems clear why he stayed away from domestic issues. This country doesn't 
deserve a good man like Clinton. It will be very interesting to see who or what 
pleases them in the future. 
</P>
<P>
 ROSE MARIE KAZANTZAKIS 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
