<P>
76ERS LIMP INTO LAKER SHOOTOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HOWARD-COOPER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Philadelphia 76ers will be without 7-foot-6 center Shawn Bradley and key 
frontcourt reserve Scott Williams for at least the rest of the exhibition 
schedule because of injuries, a stretch that begins tonight with the GTE 
Everything Pages Shootout at the Forum, the two-day tournament that also 
includes the Lakers, Orlando Magic and Denver Nuggets. 
</P>
<P>
 Bradley, returning to action after sitting out the second half of his rookie 
season because of a dislocated left kneecap and a chipped bone, hurt his knee 
again Wednesday against Minnesota in Provo, Utah, and will undergo further 
examination.Williams, signed as a free agent during the summer, has been 
bothered by back spasms. 
</P>
<P>
 The 76ers play the Nuggets today at 5 p.m., followed by the Lakers against the 
Magic at 8. Saturday, winner will play winner and loser will play loser, but 
the Lakers are in the late game no matter what. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lakers are 3-1 in exhibition play after losing, 131-113, to Seattle on 
Wednesday at San Diego. SCOTT HOWARD-COOPER 
</P>
