<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; EVENT TO RAISE FUNDS FOR COMMUNITY 
CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Community groups are throwing a hoedown and barbecue to raise funds for the 
city's planned community center. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is from 1 to 6 p.m. Saturday at Descanso Park and is being 
organized, in part, by the Seniors Club, the Boys and Girls Club of Capistrano 
Valley and other local leaders. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $10 for adults and $5 for children under 12. 
</P>
<P>
 Money raised will go toward completion of a planned 32,000-square-foot 
community center, with a gymnasium, a senior center, kitchen facilities, a 
multipurpose room and meeting rooms. 
</P>
<P>
 In August, the City Council approved $1.4 million for construction of 9,100 
square feet of the center. Information: (714) 496-9168 or (714) 495-3532.JEFF 
BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
