<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN, 26, FATALLY SHOT IN ALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 26-year-old man was shot to death in an alley Thursday morning, Los Angeles 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnny Freeman Jr. of Panorama City was pronounced dead at the scene, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting occurred about 7 a.m. near the 14300 block of Roscoe Boulevard, 
Detective Stephen Fisk said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said witnesses told them that as Freeman was walking in the 
alley, a medium-sized red four-door car drove up behind him. A man emerged, 
shot Freeman at least once, got back in the car and drove away, Fisk said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have no suspects and know of no motive. Detectives do not believe that 
Freeman was in a gang. 
</P>
