<P>
DRIVER DIES WHEN TRUCK HITS POLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 72-year-old man was killed after his pickup truck struck a power pole -- 
knocking out electricity to several hundred homes in east Palmdale, authorities 
said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Joseph Aguilar of Rosamond was driving his truck east on Avenue S near 42nd 
Street East at 10:30 p.m. Wednesday when his truck hit the pole, Sheriff's Lt. 
Terry Lewis said. 
</P>
<P>
 Aguilar, who was not wearing a seat belt, was thrown from the truck and killed 
instantly, Lewis said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident cut power to about 2,400 homes on Palmdale's east side for about 
an hour, a Southern California Edison spokeswoman said. 
</P>
