</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago College will hold a candidates forum Oct. 29 for those running 
for the county's six House of Representatives seats. 
</P>
<P>
 The free forum will be at the school's campus at Bristol and 17th streets, in 
Phillips Hall, from 10 a.m. to 12:30 p.m., spokesman Dale Ruhe said. 
</P>
<P>
 Representatives of the organizations sponsoring the event -- including the 
college's political science department, Concord Coalition of Orange County and 
the local chapter of United We Stand -- will question the candidates about the 
federal budget deficit and public debt and immigration. 
</P>
<P>
 Questions from the audience also will be taken, Ruhe said. 
</P>
