<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; 3 YOUTHS ARRESTED IN BURGLARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 8-year-old boy and two teen-agers were arrested Wednesday night on 
suspicion of stealing $4,500 worth of construction materials and causing 
$20,000 in vandalism at a new Lancaster housing tract, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The 8-year-old and a 15-year-old were released to their parents after they 
were booked for investigation of burglary and vandalism.The third boy, 14, was 
being held at the San Fernando Juvenile Hall on unrelated charges, said Los 
Angeles County Sheriff's Sgt. Richard Wood. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said all three boys allegedly knocked out windows, smashed roof 
tiles and broke water pipes at a housing tract being built by Encino-based 
Larwin Construction in the 1800 block of W. Avenue H-8 in Lancaster more than 
two weeks ago, Wood said. Graffiti also had been sprayed on some of the houses 
in the tract, he said. 
</P>
