 Mighty Duck President Tony Tavares doesn't expect the NHL lockout to result in 
layoffs of team employees "for the foreseeable future" but said workers might 
eventually be given temporary assignments -- perhaps even at Disneyland."Some 
people might be cross-utilized," said Tavares, whose team is owned by the Walt 
Disney Co. Miscellany 
</P>
