<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: PADDLERS HAHN, BRAGG BRING HOME MEDALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE HENSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bob Hahn of Ventura and Bill Bragg of Newbury Park won several age-group 
medals in the kayak competition last weekend at the World Master's Games in 
Brisbane, Australia. 
</P>
<P>
 Hahn, 50, won three gold medals, a silver and three bronze. Bragg, 57, won two 
golds and a bronze. In all, the pair competed in more than 20 races in three 
days. 
</P>
<P>
 "At this age, it's a wonderful accomplishment just to get out there," said 
Hahn, a banker. "It gives a purpose to working out." STEVE HENSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
