<HEADLINE>
<P>
EMPIRE LEAGUE FOOTBALL; VEGA'S FINAL KEY PLAY HELPS CENTURY BEAT EL DORADO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ignacio Vega's interception in the closing seconds clinched a 6-3 victory for 
Century over El Dorado in an Empire League game Thursday at Santa Ana Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Vega had several other important plays.He had a 72-yard run and a five-yard 
reception for first down on Century's scoring drive. He also had a sack from 
his defensive back position. 
</P>
<P>
 His interception came at the Century 11 with seven seconds left in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Led by quarterback Mike Marzicola and helped by a 15-yard penalty for a late 
hit, El Dorado had driven 62 yards in 27 seconds and had a first down at the 
Century 13 with 35 seconds left. Century's Robert Villegas and Luis Ramirez 
sacked Marzicola for an 11-yard loss on the next play. Marzicola, who to that 
point was four of four for 49 yards in the drive, had his next pass 
intercepted. 
</P>
<P>
 Had El Dorado been able to hang onto the ball earlier, there might not have 
been a chance for late-game heroics. The Golden Hawks fumbled on the Century 
four after opening the game with a 17-play drive that took almost 11 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 Century (3-4, 1-1 in league) then drove 94 yards for a touchdown. On third and 
seven at the Century 17, Vega went in motion, took a handoff and ran 72 yards 
to the El Dorado 11. He got an important downfield block from Jose Serratos. 
</P>
<P>
 His five-yard reception on third down gave the Centurions a first down inside 
the El Dorado one. Quarterback Stan Villanueva scored on a one-yard dive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
