<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOARA TURNS SEVEN KATELLA TURNOVERS INTO 28-7 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Loara took advantage of seven turnovers to beat Katella, 28-7, in an Empire 
League game Thursday night at Western High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Loara (3-4, 1-1) forced five fumbles, intercepted two passes and converted two 
turnovers into touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 The Saxons jumped ahead late in the first quarter after both teams struggled 
offensively. Running back Kerry Peoples scored on a three-yard run on Loara's 
third possession. 
</P>
<P>
 Katella (0-7, 0-2) fumbled on each of its next three possessions, the last 
resulting in a Loara score. Loara running back Korei Kilborn scored on an 
eight-yard run with 59 seconds left in the half to put the Saxons up, 14-0. 
</P>
<P>
 The Knights' Drew Kroger returned the ensuing kickoff 85 yards for Katella's 
only score, making the score 14-7 at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Loara started slowly in the third quarter, but struck again on their third 
possession of the half. Quarterback Jim Kirkland hit Eddie Williams on a 
12-yard touchdown pass for a 21-7 advantage. 
</P>
<P>
 Kilborn scored his second touchdown of the game on a three-yard run with five 
minutes remaining to seal the 28-7 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Kirkland completed eight of 20 passes for 92 yards and Kilborn ran for 40 
yards in 10 carries for Loara. JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
</TEXT>
