<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; VILLA PARK CLINCHES CENTURY LEAGUE GIRLS' TENNIS TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Seventh-ranked Villa Park clinched its first Century League title since 1982, 
defeating ninth-ranked Canyon for the second time in a week. The Spartans, led 
by No. 1 singles player Faye DeVera's three victories, defeated Canyon, 12-6, 
Thursday after a 10-8 victory a week ago. 
</P>
<P>
 "This was convincing," Villa Park Coach Sue Gardiner said. "These kids have 
what it takes. They're not letting down against anyone and they're not letting 
anything slip away." 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park (12-1, 8-0 in league) leads Canyon (13-3, 5-3) by three games and 
second-place El Modena, which has been beaten twice by Villa Park, by two games 
with two matches left. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to DeVera's sweep, Villa Park got three victories from its No. 1 
and No. 2 doubles teams of Jill Riley and Shawn Lerer and Susan Shaw and Carrie 
Ota. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon received two of its six points from No. 1 singles player Shannon 
Wilkins. DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
