<P>
MT. SAC CROSS-COUNTRY MEET BEGINS TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The nation's largest high school cross-country event, the 46th Mt. San Antonio 
College Invitational, begins today and continues Saturday on the college's 
campus in Walnut. 
</P>
<P>
 Today's competition, which features Division III and IV schools, begins at 
2:45 p.m. Saturday's races, featuring Division I and II schools, begin at 8 
a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra, ranked No. 7 in the Orange County sportswriters' poll, Newport 
Harbor (No. 8) and El Modena (No. 10) will be featured in the boys' Division 
III race today at 5:20 p.m. The Division III girls' race, which begins at 5:40, 
features El Modena (No. 6), Foothill and Newport Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
 Saturday's sweepstakes boys' race, which will be run at 9:30 a.m., features 
the state's top teams regardless of division. County entrants include Santa Ana 
Valley (No. 4), Santa Ana (No. 5), Edison and Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
 The girls' sweepstakes race, at 10:30, is highlighted by the county's top four 
ranked teams -- No. 1 Irvine, No. 2 El Toro, No. 3 Esperanza and No. 4 Edison 
-- plus No. 10 Santa Ana Valley. MATT FARMER 
</P>
