<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; OCC WINS ITS EIGHTH IN A ROW IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange Coast (14-5-1, 4-0) earned its eighth consecutive water polo victory 
Thursday, defeating Palomar, 19-5, in an Orange Empire Conference game at 
Orange Coast. 
</P>
<P>
 Palomar (3-16, 0-3) trailed by one with 3 minutes 15 seconds left in the 
first, but Orange Coast scored eight consecutive goals to take an 11-2 lead 
with 4:56 left in the half. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Orange Empire Conference water polo: 
</P>
<P>
 Grossmont 20, Saddleback 7 -- John Giulianotti scored 10 goals to lead host 
Grossmont (22-4, 4-0). Blake Corbin led Saddleback (9-12, 2-2) with two goals. 
</P>
