<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLDEN WEST TO FACE SOUTHWESTERN TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golden West, with its top two tailbacks out for the season, takes on 
Southwestern in a Mission Conference Central Division game at 7 tonight at 
Orange Coast College. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West (1-4-1, 1-1) began the year with Thomas Green and Mark Crowley 
rotating at tailback.Green was hurt early and left the team after four games. 
Crowley was coming off a career-high 147 yards, but broke his ankle on his 
first carry Saturday in a 35-14 loss to Rancho Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
 Damien Cook and John Sims figure to rotate at tailback tonight with Timm Wynn 
at fullback. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West quarterback Brian Schneider hasn't had a pass intercepted. He is 
82 of 166 for 889 yards with eight touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Southwestern (0-4-1, 0-1-1) is coming off a 47-7 loss at Riverside and has 
allowed a conference-high 29 touchdowns. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
