<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AEROSPACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Aerospace Corp. to Lay Off 150: The nonprofit research and development concern 
said the work force cuts, effective Nov. 4, represent 5% of the firm's 3,320 
employees. The El Segundo-based company said the layoffs stem from reduced 
funding from the Defense Department, at $335 million in the fiscal year that 
began Oct. 1 from $360 million the prior year. Aerospace Corp. said its 
employment has fallen 25% since 1990 because of steady declines in federal 
funding. 
</P>
