PEOPLE: FIRST INTERSTATE CHOOSES SIART TO REPLACE OUTGOING CHAIRMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 First Interstate Bancorp named William Siart, 47, its president since 1990, to 
replace Edward M. Carson as chairman and chief executive when Carson retires in 
May. 
</P>
<P>
 Siart's promotion to the bank holding company's two top spots was widely 
expected.Carson, who has headed Los Angeles-based First Interstate for the last 
four years, will turn 65 in November. 
</P>
<P>
 Analysts expect few changes in the bank's corporate strategy. Last month, both 
executives said they did not want to turn First Interstate into a nationwide 
banking empire and will instead concentrate on building a "super-regional" bank 
that does business primarily in the West. 
</P>
<P>
 Siart, like Carson, is also expected to want to keep First Interstate 
independent. Both men have voiced their opposition to informal merger proposals 
made by Wells Fargo Bank over the past year. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Prudential Insurance Co. of America elected Arthur F. Ryan, president and 
chief operating officer of Chase Manhattan Bank, as its new chairman. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan, 52, will join the largest U.S. life insurer on Nov. 1. He will succeed 
Robert C. Winters, 62, as chairman and CEO on Dec. 1. 
</P>
