<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: CHIEF EXECUTIVE APPOINTED AT TOSHIBA AMERICA SYSTEMS 
UNIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Joseph A. Cleary has been appointed chief executive of Topac U.S.A. Inc., a 
wholly owned subsidiary of Toshiba America Information Systems Inc. in Irvine 
that provides a new distribution channel for the office automation industry. 
Cleary was previously vice president of business operations for Alco Office 
Products.Before that, he was with Xerox Corp. for more than 20 years, holding 
several senior management positions in its sales and marketing divisions. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Stan Dreyfuss has joined Kemper Securities Inc. as a vice president for 
investments in the Newport Beach office. He had previously been vice president 
for investments at Smith Barney. Before that, Dreyfuss was West Coast managing 
director for Citicorp Investments International in the Los Angeles office. 
</P>
