<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; NETHERLANDS; DOCUMENTARY FIRST TO SHOW EUTHANASIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A documentary chronicling the mercy killing of a severely debilitated man was 
shown on Dutch television in the first known filming of euthanasia in the 
Netherlands.The one-hour documentary, "Death Upon Request," told the story of 
Cees van Wendel de Joode, who suffered from the degenerative muscle disorder 
Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis, also known as Lou Gehrig's Disease. Van Wendel 
de Joode was believed to be 55. While mercy killing is still officially illegal 
in the Netherlands, doctors are guaranteed immunity from prosecution if they 
follow the euthanasia policy, the most liberal in the industrialized world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
