<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: BANKING AND FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by James S. Granelli, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Onyx Sells Securities: Onyx Acceptance Corp., an Irvine company specializing 
in automobile finance, said it has sold $38.6 million in securities backed by 
the automobiles it finances. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's management should have some experience at creating such 
securities. It's an offshoot of Western Financial Savings Bank in Irvine, which 
pioneered the sale of securities backed by automobile loans. 
</P>
