<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEDIA FORUM TO COVER 'HEADLINE HYSTERIA' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Television journalists Edwin Newman and Linda Ellerbee, actor Edward James 
Olmos, Superior Court Judge Aviva Bobb and L.A. Times Media Critic David Shaw 
are among those scheduled to take part in "What Signals Are the Media Sending 
You?," an Oct. 27 educational forum hosted by Pacific Clinics Diamond Circle 
and the Caltech Y. 
</P>
<P>
 Scheduled for 8 p.m. at Caltech's Beckman Auditorium, the forum will focus on 
"headline hysteria" and how it may affect public policy and fear of violence. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is $25. Information: (818) 795-8471. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102194-0345 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 090907 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
